title: State football: Towson scores last-minute touchdown to top Stony Brook, 21-14
text:
(Edward Lee) 
The win marks the fourth in a row for Bowie State. 
Franklin & Marshall 30, McDaniel 28: The visiting Diplomats (5-1, 4-1 Centennial Conference) built a 23-7 halftime lead before holding on to beat the Green Terror (0-6, 0-5). 
Will Koester completed 22 of 32 passes for 267 yards in his first start for McDaniel, throwing three touchdowns. Mike Oliveto caught eight passes for 131 yards. 
Frostburg State 19, The College of New Jersey 3: Isaac Robinson made field goals of 32 and 30 yards, and the host Bobcats (5-1, 4-1 New Jersey Athletic Conference) won their fourth straight game. The Lions fell to 0-5, 0-4. 
Salisbury 62, William Paterson 33: The host Sea Gulls (4-1, 4-0 NJAC) put up 744 total offensive yards and beat the Pioneers (1-5, 0-5). 
Four Salisbury players rushed for two touchdowns each: Jerome Johnson, Connor Canonico, Ryan Jones and Dandre Dennis. 

TOWSON 21, STONY BROOK 14
